Booking appointments for clinics can be a difficult task. There are two methods that people usually employ to book an appointment. First they can contact the clinic by phone and find the next available time through verbal communication or try their luck and just walk-in to the clinic and hope that there is a short queue waiting. However, these methods are very inefficient. </br> </br> \
\
Talking on the phone could lead to misunderstanding as it is not visual but verbal. People could misunderstand the time for appointment due to bad reception or poor listening. Furthermore, for some people who have multiple bookings with several clinics it could be hard to keep track of all of them. </br> </br> \
\
Another problem is that when we go to see a new doctor, we waste precious time by explaining to them what conditions we have had before (your medical history) and the doctors will take notes and file up the report. Additionally, we sometimes need to bring the report to another doctor for further examination. This process can easily become messy and lead to errors if the documents were not delivered correctly.\
