\b The user
\b0 \

\f0  A hypothesis persona was used throughout the design process making sure the end product fits the needs of the user.  It reflects the problems in a practical way during the envision stage. \

\f1 \

\f0  Aside from the persona, several interviews and discussions were conducted with health professionals; including two doctors, an optometrist, and a physiotherpist. The interviews helped me to gain a better understandings of how current systems lack of and the needs of both the medical team and the patient. \
\
Several real life cases were addressed during the interview. The general practitioner mentioned that when working with chronic illness patients, the health team would always ask their patients to measure their blood pressure and blood sugar level every day and write on a notebook to bring back for follow-up. However this method is not instant and often elder patients would forget. \
\
The optometrist also shared that, often when they ask patients what medications they\'92re currently taking, they would bring in a piece of paper with scribbles- which can lead to misunderstanding. For patients with conditions such as rheumatoid arthritis, her team would attach test result and refer them to specialist. If would be easier for them if there a system that the health team could attach photos or PDF on the cloud to communicate with each other. \
